19:08.088 --> 19:23.390
[SPEAKER_00]: But the general also had under his command a newly formed unit called the Second Ranger Battalion, which was Camp Forest, Tennessee near Chattanooga, and it was not progressing well.

19:23.410 --> 19:31.060
[SPEAKER_00]: And so he he picked up selected rudder on the basis of what he saw of rudders training program in 83rd Division.

19:31.341 --> 19:36.508
[SPEAKER_00]: He picked out rudder to become the commanding officer of the Second Ranger Battalion.

19:36.691 --> 19:57.657
[SPEAKER_00]: So Rudder then moved to the 2nd Ranger Battalion and through there in Tennessee and amphibious training in Florida and finally up the East Coast to board the Queen Elizabeth in New York Harbor in late November of 43, that's the state-side training period.

19:58.198 --> 20:03.084
[SPEAKER_00]: In England, he arrived without knowing what his mission would be.

20:03.965 --> 20:06.208
[SPEAKER_00]: At the time, everyone knew

20:06.796 --> 20:15.016
[SPEAKER_00]: that there would be an attack from Britain across the English Channel on the French coast in the spring of 44.

20:16.379 --> 20:18.664
[SPEAKER_00]: He didn't know what his mission was.

